Ini Dia Salat Tarawih Terlama di Indonesia, Selesai Langsung Sahur! Salat tarawih yang dilaksanakan di Pondok Pesantren Al-Fatah, Desa Temboro, Kecamatan Karas, Kabupaten Magetan ini dilakukan dalam durasi waktu 8 jam! Salat tarawih di ponpes Al-Fatah benar-benar berlangsung selama 8 jam. Tepatnya sehabis Isya dan baru berakhir pada pukul 03.30 WIB atau menjelang waktu sahur. Tradisi salat tarawih terlama ini merupakan tradisi turun temurun yang sudah dilakukan 10 tahun terakhir. Pimpinan Madrasah Aliyah dan pengurus Ponpes Al-Fatah Temboro Ustaz Barrlei Musaddad mengatakan bahwa awalnya salat tarawih yang seperti ini hanya dilakukan oleh ustad senior bersama beberapa santrinya secara diam-diam. Awalnya belum ada peminatnya. Namun seiring berjalannya waktu, makin banyak orang yang ingin ikut. Saking banyaknya jamaah yang ingin ikut salat tarawih ini, pelaksanaannya tidak dilakukan dalam satu masjid, melainkan dibagi jadi beberapa majelis (kelompok) dan tersebar di seluruh masjid yang ada di sekitar ponpes dan juga masjid lingkungan masyarakat desa.    #shalattarawih #tarawihterlama #ponpesalfatahtemboro

video_description: The exposure of UNRWA (United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in the Near East) has shed light on significant challenges within the organization. UNRWA, tasked with providing essential services to Palestinian refugees, has faced scrutiny over allegations of mismanagement, corruption, and politicization of aid. Revelations regarding financial misappropriation, misconduct among staff, and perpetuation of dependency cycles have raised concerns about the effectiveness and integrity of UNRWA's operations. The exposure has prompted calls for accountability, transparency, and structural reforms to ensure that humanitarian assistance reaches those most in need while upholding the principles of neutrality and impartiality. As efforts to address these issues continue, there is a pressing need to prioritize the well-being and rights of Palestinian refugees, ensuring that they receive the support and services they require for dignified living conditions and sustainable futures.

video_description: The United Nations Agency for Palestine Refugees also known as the UNRWA is the primary humanitarian agency in Gaza, with over 2 million people depending on it for their â€œsheer survivalâ€. (UNRWA Commissioner general) â€¯ The Agency runs shelters for over 1 million people and provides food and primary healthcare.â€¯They have been the main supplier of food, water and shelter in Gaza since October (abc news) So why is the United states along with along with Canada, Australia, Britain, Germany, Italy, the Netherlands, Switzerland, Finland, and Japan halting their funding, which together account for over 60% of the agencies total funds. ( al Jazeera ) A move that A UN-appointed expert on the right to food, Michael Fakhri, warns will mean famine is now inevitable in Gaza.(Reuters) This funding has been halted in response to accusations against twelve UNRWA staff members in Gaza and as Commissioner-General Lazzarini shared  â€œIt is shocking to see a suspension of funds to the Agency in reaction to allegations against a small group of staff, especially given the immediate action that UNRWA took by terminating their contracts and asking for a transparent independent investigation," Lazzarini has urged countries that have suspended funding to UNRWA to reconsider before the agency "is forced to suspend its humanitarian response." In Gaza U.N. Secretary-General Antonio Guterres says 2 million Palestinians in Gaza, which is 87% of the population, rely on UNRWA services that would be scaled back as soon as February if the money is not restored. (Time) "Although aid can reach Gaza through other agencies such as the International Committee of the Red Cross, the key infrastructure for delivering aid in Gaza is through UNRWA. Revelations regarding financial misappropriation, misconduct among staff, and perpetuation of dependency cycles have raised concerns about the effectiveness and integrity of UNRWA's operations. The exposure has prompted calls for accountability, transparency, and structural reforms to ensure that humanitarian assistance reaches those most in need while upholding the principles of neutrality and impartiality. As efforts to address these issues continue, there is a pressing need to prioritize the well-being and rights of Palestinian refugees, ensuring that they receive the support and services they require for dignified living conditions and sustainable futures.
